<section class="bg-gray-50 py-12">
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <div class="text-center mb-8 px-6">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">Accessibility Statement</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mt-4">
      <strong>Queue Development LLC</strong> is committed to providing a website that is accessible to the widest possible audience,
      regardless of technology or ability. We are actively working to increase the accessibility and usability of our website
      and in doing so adhere to many of the available standards and guidelines.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="container mx-auto px-6 space-y-12">
    <!-- Conformance Target -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Conformance Target</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Our goal is to conform to the <strong>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2 Level AA</strong>.
        These guidelines explain how to make web content more accessible for people with disabilities and more usable for everyone.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Efforts to Support Accessibility -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">What We’re Doing</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Embedding accessibility in design and development (semantic HTML, ARIA where appropriate, color-contrast checks).</li>
        <li>Supporting keyboard-only navigation and visible focus states across interactive components.</li>
        <li>Providing text alternatives for non-text content and captions/transcripts for time-based media where applicable.</li>
        <li>Using headings, landmarks, and consistent navigation patterns across pages.</li>
        <li>Testing with automated tools and assistive tech (e.g., screen readers) during major updates.</li>
        <li>Training our team on accessibility best practices and inclusive content writing.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Compatibility & Limitations -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Compatibility &amp; Limitations</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The site is designed to work with the latest versions of major browsers (Chrome, Edge, Firefox, Safari) and on modern
        operating systems (Windows, macOS, iOS, Android). Some older browsers or unsupported assistive technologies may not provide
        the best experience.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Third-party content</strong> (e.g., embedded videos, maps, social widgets) may not fully meet our target.
        We encourage vendors to provide accessible alternatives and will assist with remediation where feasible.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Alternative Formats -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Alternative Formats</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        If you need content in an alternative format (e.g., accessible PDF, large print), contact us and we’ll provide it in a
        reasonable timeframe.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Feedback & Contact -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Feedback &amp; Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our website. If you encounter an accessibility barrier,
        please let us know:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Contact form: <a href="/contact" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">/contact</a></li>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:support@queuedevelop.com" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">support@queuedevelop.com</a></li>
        <li class="text-sm text-gray-500">If you prefer phone assistance, let us know via email and we’ll schedule a call.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Assessment & Review -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Assessment &amp; Review</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        We review this statement and re-test key user journeys at least once per year and after significant releases.
        <span class="block mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500"><strong>Last reviewed:</strong> Oct 17, 2025</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
